At the southern intersection of Main Street (Jaggar Ave.) and Kissena Blvd (Jamaica Ave.), showing the new Carnegie Library.

About 1906.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

28 Kissena Boulevard, east side, between Forty-first and Barclay Avenues, showing the C.P. Leggett house of 1873. To the left of this house stood the dwelling purchased by the St. George P.E. parish for the parsonage in 1838. The rear of the home was on Forty-first Avenue. All the remains indicating where the parsonage stood in 1922 are the stone steps and walk leading to it.
1922
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
